    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine Domini Dei Salvatoris nostri Iesu Christi. Domnus <persName
                            ref="#people/303" key="#Princeps">Arichis</persName> piissimus atque
                        excellentissimus <rs key="#Princeps">princeps</rs> gentis Langubardorum,
                        divino premonitus nutu, offero in <orgName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Wine #Churches #Slave"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/85"><rs key="#Churches">ecclesia</rs> Sancte
                            Sophię</orgName> quam a fundamentis edificavi, pro redemptione anime meę
                        seu pro salvatione gentis nostre et patrie, <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Slave"
                            >servos et ancillas</rs> nec non et <rs
                            key="#Wine #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >vineas</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >territoria</rs> quantum <name ref="Munepadus">Munepadu</name>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbyter</rs> in <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3416"><rs key="#Churches">ęcclesia</rs> Sancti
                            Petri <placeName ref="#places/3446"
                                key="#Villages/settlements #Fiscal_property">ad Aqua
                                Sancta</placeName></orgName> laborare visus est, ad nostram
                        pertincxit potestatem, unde omnia et in omnibus Sancte Sophie <rs
                            key="#Monasteries">monasterio</rs> concessimus possidendum, seu <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3417" key="#Fiscal_property #Churches"><rs
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                                >ecclesia</rs> Sancti Stephani</orgName> in <geogName key="#Gai"
                            ref="#estates/3407"><rs key="#Gai">gaio</rs> nostro Fecline</geogName>
                        eidem monasterio Sancte Sophię concessimus perfruendum. Quod vero preceptus
                        oblationis ex iussione et dictatus nominate potestatis scripsi ego <persName
                            key="#Notary" ref="#people/3410">Lopoald</persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs>. Actus <placeName key="#Cities"
                            ref="#places/110">Beneventus</placeName> in filicissimo <rs
                            key="#Palatium">palatio</rs> in anno septimo decimo, mensi novembrio per
                        indictionem tertiam decimam. Feliciter.</ab> 
                    <ab><note>Nel cartulario è presente anche un riassunto del
                        documento, inserito nel falso <foreign>preceptum donationum,
                            concessionum et confirmationum</foreign> del novembre 774 
                        (CSS, (†) I, 1, pp. 289-336), per il quale si veda il commento al 
                        doc. 3535. Segue il testo di detto riassunto (CSS, I, 1 [35], p. 315):</note></ab> 
                    <ab>(…) [35] Nec non et servos seu et ancillas et vineas et territoria quantum 
                        Munepaldus presbyter in ęcclesia Sancti Petri ad Aqua Sancta lavore visus est 
                        ad nostram pertinxit potestatem, unde omnia et in omnibus Sancte Sofie monasterio 
                        concessimus possidendum; seu et ecclesia Sancti Stephani in gaio nostro Fecline 
                        eidem monasterio Sancte Sophie concessimus possidendum.(…)</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
